","time":1399289575}, {"aspects":[{"rating":2,"type":"overall"}],"author_name":"Steve Harrison","author_url":"https://plus.google.com/102040367371722836773","language":"en","rating":4,"text":"I made a booking and then was a bit worried after reading some of the reviews on here.

We had our overnight stay in a very nice grand hotel, with a nice room looking out over the gardens with views of York Minster in the distance and the river, the wall around York and York itself. 
Its in a very good position, next to the train station, ideal if arriving by train and just as easy to get to by car.

Very helpful staff, nice room, great breakfast in a dining room with lots of room, pool and gym available, and on site parking although there is a charge for parking like most hotels in York.
The position of the hotel means you are only a few minutes walk away from most things in York so ideal for tourist to this great city.

Why only 4 stars? 
We had a 30 minute wait for our room to be ready. We arrived early at 11:30am and checked in and was told room would be ready at 3pm which we expected. We then went in to York, came back at 3:30pm only to be told we would have to wait a bit longer which we did in the hotel bar. 
The bar was quite expensive and this was the only time we had a drink in there. 
The staff did keep us informed and brought our room key to us as soon as the room was ready for us.
These are the only reasons for not giving the hotel 5 star rating.

Very Good Hotel with Great Staff.
